---
title: Mojo Pork Tacos with Creamy Cilantro Slaw
description: As if you needed another reason to celebrate taco night, this version’s ready in ten. minutes. flat. (Yes, you read that right!) Ground pork simmers in a sweet, tangy, citrusy Cuban mojo sauce, then gets stuffed into steamy tortillas. It’s topped with a creamy slaw and sprinkled with cilantro, then served with lime wedges for squeezing over. Ready, set, TACO!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mojo-pork-tacos-fe9f37ee.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mojo-pork-tacos-5ef10b210cb7523faf37e696-711c5912.pdf
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
time required: 10 minutes
cuisine: Carribean
nutrition:
  calories: 940 kcal
  fat: 54 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1490 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mojo-pork-tacos-5ef10b210cb7523faf37e696
---

Wash and dry all produce.

Halve @orange{1}. Halve 1 @lime{2} and quarter remaining lime. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in a large #pan{} over high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

> 4 SERVINGS: Halve both oranges. Halve 2 limes and quarter remaining limes.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

While pork cooks, squeeze juice from whole orange and 1 lime half into a small #bowl{}. Stir in @cumin{1%tsp}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, @dried oregano{1%tsp}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and @sugar{1%tsp}.

Once pork is browned, pour in mojo sauce. Cook until sauce has reduced and pork is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 tsp sugar.

Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the cilantro, 2 packets @sour cream{6%tbsp} (save the rest for serving), and a pinch of remaining garlic powder to taste.

Add @coleslaw mix{4%ounce} to bowl; toss to coat. Add a big squeeze of lime juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 4 packets sour cream.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with pork mixture (leave any excess sauce in pan), slaw, and remaining sour cream. Garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.